cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.CL 

The paper presents a new auto-augmentation framework for point cloud classification, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses an adversarial learning strategy and formulates a learnable point augmentation function, which are related to artificial intelligence (AI) and graphics (GR) sub-fields. Finally, the paper also discusses the design of loss functions, which is relevant to computational linguistics (CL) sub-field.
